comment:
* Class to hold NfcF service info.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: mDynamicSystemCode
variables.comment: * System Code of the service registered by API

variables.name: mDynamicNfcid2
variables.comment: * NFCID2 of the service registered by API

variables.name: mUid
variables.comment: * The uid of the package the service belongs to

methods.name: public ComponentName getComponent()
methods.comment:
* Returns the app component corresponding to this NFCF service.
     *
     * @return app component for this service

methods.name: public String getSystemCode()
methods.comment:
* Returns the system code corresponding to this service.
     *
     * @return system code for this service

methods.name: public void setDynamicSystemCode(@NonNull String systemCode)
methods.comment:
* Add or replace a system code to this service.
     * @param systemCode system code to set or replace

methods.name: public String getNfcid2()
methods.comment:
* Returns NFC ID2.
     *
     * @return nfc id2 to return

methods.name: public void setDynamicNfcid2(@NonNull String nfcid2)
methods.comment:
* Set or replace NFC ID2
     *
     * @param nfcid2 NFC ID2 string

methods.name: public String getDescription()
methods.comment:
* Returns description of service.
     * @return user readable description of service

methods.name: public int getUid()
methods.comment:
* Returns uid of service.
     * @return uid of the service

methods.name: public String getT3tPmm()
methods.comment:
* Returns LF_T3T_PMM of the service
     * @return returns LF_T3T_PMM of the service

methods.name: public CharSequence loadLabel(@NonNull PackageManager pm)
methods.comment:
* Load application label for this service.
     * @param pm packagemanager instance
     * @return label name corresponding to service

methods.name: public Drawable loadIcon(@NonNull PackageManager pm)
methods.comment:
* Load application icon for this service.
     * @param pm packagemanager instance
     * @return app icon corresponding to service

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
public void dump(@NonNull ParcelFileDescriptor fd, @NonNull PrintWriter pw, @NonNull String[] args)
methods.comment:
* Dump contents of the service for debugging.
     * @param fd parcelfiledescriptor instance
     * @param pw printwriter instance
     * @param args args for dumping

methods.name: public void dumpDebug(@NonNull ProtoOutputStream proto)
methods.comment:
* Dump debugging info as NfcFServiceInfoProto.
     *
     * If the output belongs to a sub message, the caller is responsible for wrapping this function
     * between {@link ProtoOutputStream#start(long)} and {@link ProtoOutputStream#end(long)}.
     *
     * @param proto the ProtoOutputStream to write to

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
public void dump(@NonNull ParcelFileDescriptor fd, @NonNull PrintWriter pw, @NonNull String[] args)
